Specimen Examined for
Georgia Atlas Project
18 July 2009 (handwritten)

Plants of the Etowah River Basin of Georgia
Dawson County

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata*
Galax
(Poir.) Brummit

Dawson Forest Wildlife Management Area, Wildcat Creek Tract, accessed from jeep trail just west of Pleasant Union Church, off of Steve Tate Hwy, 1.9 miles S. of Fausett Lake on State Hwy 136. Survey begins at confluence of Amicalola and Wildcat Cr.

Growing in scattered clumps in leaf litter, on top of knob over Wildcat Cr., edge of north-facing slope. Common. Growing with *Chimaphila maculata*. North-west facing slope. Canopy of *Quercus velutina*, *Quercus prinus*, *Quercus coccinea*, *Pinus strobus*, *Oxydendrum arboreum*.

Lisa Kruse 01 - 266a                                                                 11 June 2001

IMAGED 2013


*Galax urceolata*
